  "event_preview": "Circuit de Monaco is a 3.337 km (2.074 mi) street circuit in Monte Carlo with 19 corners. The 2026 Formula 2 Monaco round is the fourth of 12 rounds on the calendar, held June 4-7 as a support to the Formula One Monaco Grand Prix. The weekend features a sprint race on Saturday and a feature race on Sunday.\n\nGabriele Minì leads the championship by 19 points heading to Monaco, showing consistency through scoring points in every race so far. Nikola Tsolov is the season's only multiple winner with victories at Melbourne and Miami, and arrives with significant psychological advantage — he has won the Formula 3 race at Monaco for the past two consecutive years and will be hunting a third. Colton Herta, the nine-time IndyCar winner on his partial-season F2 schedule, continues his pursuit of a Super Licence. Rafael Câmara remains competitive after his early-season performances.\n\nThe all-time Formula 2 qualifying record at Monaco belongs to Théo Pourchaire, who set a 1:20.985 during the 2021 Hyperpole session. The race fastest lap record is held by Zhou Guanyu, who clocked a 1:21.912 during the 2021 feature race.",
